House Resolution 413
By: Representative Au of the 50th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Communities in Schools of Atlanta; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Communities in Schools of Atlanta (CIS of Atlanta) places caring adults inside
3 schools to create a consistent academic, emotional, and financial support system to help
4 students stay in school and graduate; and
5 WHEREAS, CIS of Atlanta's mission is to surround students with a community of support,
6 empowering them to remain in school and achieve success in life by collaborating with
7 teachers, parents, and community partners to meet each student's unique needs; and
8 WHEREAS, CIS of Atlanta currently serves students across six metro Atlanta school
9 districts—Atlanta Public Schools, Fulton County, DeKalb County, Decatur City Schools,
10 Clayton County, and Griffin-Spalding County—by providing essential services that foster
11 a positive school environment and address school-wide risk factors; and
12 WHEREAS, among the 49,000 students served during the 2023-2024 school year, those
13 receiving intensive individualized support from CIS of Atlanta totaled 3,914, with 99 percent
14 remaining in school and 98 percent graduating or being promoted to the next grade level,
15 surpassing the average by 14 percent; and
